VERDICT: REJECTED
The task should not be marked complete: the diff contains substantial functional code changes (not “no changes”), and there are blocking implementation issues.

Critical findings:
- The submitted summary is inconsistent with the actual commit scope. Since base `cb71e38`, ~2.6k LOC were added/modified across frontend/backend (new customer API client, controllers/routes/services/repositories, schema changes, DB scripts). This is not a no-op setup task.
- Frontend integration is incomplete: `apps/customer-web/src/app/CustomerApp.tsx` (new API-driven app) is added but not wired into the running app. `apps/customer-web/src/app/App.tsx` still renders its own in-file `CustomerApp` implementation with mock/static data, so the new API layer and behavior are effectively unused.
- Server ESM compatibility risk introduced in schema imports: multiple files changed from `./x.js` to extensionless `./x` in `server/src/database/schema/*`. In this project’s Node ESM runtime (`type: module`), compiled JS typically requires explicit extensions; this can break `dist` runtime resolution.

Security: none observed at serious/blocking level in the reviewed diff.

Next actions:
1) Reconcile task scope and commit history: either reset/rebase task #1 to true setup-only changes, or update task intent and re-review as a feature task.
2) If feature work is intended, wire `App.tsx` to use the new `CustomerApp.tsx` and validate end-to-end flows against real `/api` endpoints.
3) Standardize server import specifiers for ESM runtime compatibility (use explicit `.js` for transpiled imports, including schema barrel/internal imports) and run a full build/start verification before resubmission.

